Ask HN: Should I hire a CTO or two founding engineers?
text:
Hi HN - I'm a nontechnical founder currently building a marketplace, am getting early customer validation talking to users, and have capital committed ahead of our first round of funding from Angels.

Have solo founders in similar situations approached derisking their company by hiring 1 early CTO or finding 2 founding engineers?

I'm leaning towards CTO but want to double-check for feedback here. Part of the reason I'm looking to add to the technical side now is to build the initial version of the product beyond the spreadsheets I have and make us more likely to get into YC.

Regardless we'll keep burn low so it's enough cash for this person to meet minimum living needs and more upside play with equity until we hit milestones for the next round and then can raise cash comp.

Thanks in advance for your feedback.

Show HN: blanco.ai (YC S23) Ad Management. Automated
text:
Hi I am Orlando founder of blanco (https://www.blanco-media.ai/). Were automate social media ad management for small businesses. We have taken the advertising agency model of managing ads and put it into a software product. We provide far greater performance as we can analyse data 24/7 have 98% lower costs than agencies (we start at just $49/month compared to agencies at $2.5-$12k/month) and you can get started in just 10 minutes with our streamlined onboarding.

We have made and end to end solution from creating the ads to managing the ads. Ad copy is done by GPT-3 so you can just type in your first ideal version and then we will generate multiple others. We allow you to create graphic ads on our site using our ad generator, creating high quality, converting ads for your business.

For managing ads dynamically A/B test all of your title, image and description combinations to see what preforms best with your target audience and then optimise the budget to the ads that preform well. We also look at metrics like cost-per-action to optimise ads which convert your desired goal (e.g. product sales) for the lowest price possible.

So far we have over 100 small businesses effectively managing their ad campaigns with us. Providing greater performance for a fraction of the price. I saw that agencies were expensive and ineffective and so I created blanco.

If you need to run ads for your website or business then we would love to hear feedback from you. The first month is free only for the next 5 days.

https://www.blanco-media.ai/

Ukrainian startup Uspacy has entered the international markets
text:
Ukrainian b2b-startup Uspacy has announced its entry into the international markets.

Entrepreneurs who already understand the need to manage company processes can find many tools to help them with it. But the problem is that people don't really want to use many different products — they want to use all tools in one product.

Uspacy is an online service, a single digital workspace for organizing the daily processes of small and medium-sized companies which are: modern communication in a team, people operations, collaboration, tasks, business processes and CRM.

Registration is available at addresses uspacy.com and uspacy.eu.

Show HN: scikit-learn-ts Auto-generated TS wrapper around Python's #1 ML library
text:
Python's ML ecosystem is generally much more mature than the JS/TS ML ecosystem.

As a primarily full-stack TS dev, I've seen first-hand how difficult it is to perform simple ML-related tasks that the Python community takes for granted.

So I decided to try an experiment: how well would it work to auto-generate a TypeScript wrapper around Python's scikit-learn package, using a Python subprocess and IPC to communicate back and forth between them?

Turns out it works really well in practice, and so scikit-learn-ts was born.

The library supports all 257 classes exported by the official Python scikit-learn, and their TS wrappers are all auto-generated from the Python API docs.

This project's a lil hacky, but I've already reached out to the scikit-learn team, and we may experiment with using Pyodide as an alternative backend for the Python bridge.

Looking for feedback & ideas to improve the project. Thanks! :)
